Undergrads Take Arts Management Trek to NYC
Undergraduate students at Goizueta along with arts majors in Emory College were treated to an insider‚Äôs tour of New York City‚Äôs art scene earlier this year, during the first Arts Management Trek to the Big Apple. The trek is part of the four-year-old Arts Management concentration, which allows students majoring in dance, music, theater and arts history, as well as BBA students who are passionate about those areas, to deepen their perspective and competencies at the intersection of the arts and business.
